<text top="48" left="221" width="767" height="54" font="3">Four broad categories of censorship</text>
<text top="166" left="221" width="250" height="34" font="4"><i>Speaker by a state</i></text>
<text top="202" left="275" width="10" height="34" font="5">•</text>
<text top="202" left="329" width="865" height="34" font="5">The Government doesn’t let its citizens say something (achieved </text>
<text top="238" left="329" width="565" height="34" font="5">through legal or technical means normally)</text>
<text top="274" left="221" width="245" height="34" font="4"><i>Listener by a state</i></text>
<text top="310" left="275" width="10" height="34" font="5">•</text>
<text top="310" left="329" width="884" height="34" font="5">The Government doesn’t let it’s citizens hear something (achieved </text>
<text top="346" left="329" width="565" height="34" font="5">through legal or technical means normally)</text>
<text top="382" left="221" width="325" height="34" font="4"><i>Speaker by private actor</i></text>
<text top="418" left="275" width="10" height="34" font="5">•</text>
<text top="418" left="329" width="833" height="34" font="5">A person or company doesn’t let you say something (achieved </text>
<text top="454" left="329" width="443" height="34" font="5">though the legal means normally)</text>
<text top="490" left="221" width="320" height="34" font="4"><i>Listener by private actor</i></text>
<text top="526" left="275" width="10" height="34" font="5">•</text>
<text top="526" left="329" width="893" height="34" font="5">A person or company doesn’t let you hear something (through…..?)</text>
