<text top="82" left="263" width="525" height="54" font="1">The History of Education</text>
<text top="174" left="246" width="900" height="34" font="8">The Romans introduced formal (fee paying) schools using methods </text>
<text top="210" left="246" width="331" height="34" font="8">adopted from the Greeks</text>
<text top="246" left="246" width="712" height="34" font="8">• Boys and girls educated – not necessarily together</text>
<text top="282" left="246" width="470" height="34" font="8">• Sons of rich men went to Athens</text>
<text top="354" left="246" width="845" height="34" font="8">The European  Dark Ages mainly had only practical education –</text>
<text top="390" left="246" width="328" height="34" font="8">fighting, hunting, farming</text>
<text top="426" left="246" width="867" height="34" font="8">• The Church owned the only books – The Bible copied by hand</text>
<text top="462" left="246" width="870" height="34" font="8">• Common people were not educated so very low rate of literacy</text>
<text top="498" left="246" width="531" height="34" font="8">• Oxford University founded late 1100s</text>
</page>
