<text top="170" left="328" width="810" height="39" font="12"><i>“Tell me and I forget, teach me and I may remember, </i></text>
<text top="212" left="550" width="358" height="39" font="12"><i>involve me and I learn.”</i></text>
<text top="294" left="856" width="11" height="39" font="13">-</text>
<text top="294" left="910" width="276" height="39" font="13">Benjamin Franklin</text>
<text top="365" left="272" width="907" height="39" font="13">Good educational practice is to get students to engage in a </text>
<text top="406" left="272" width="548" height="39" font="13">variety of different forms of learning </text>
<text top="447" left="272" width="912" height="39" font="13">• Old models of learner types (auditory, visual, kinesthetic) </text>
<text top="489" left="312" width="806" height="39" font="13">aren’t real but they are a <i>useful lie  </i>if you teach to all </text>
<text top="530" left="312" width="88" height="39" font="13">styles</text>
<text top="82" left="263" width="330" height="54" font="1">Learning Styles</text>
</page>
